      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOKKAIDO EXPRESS (3) missed the hat-trick last start when third and beaten 4.5 lengths (25.81) last time at Ballarat. Can find winning form. GRAFFITI (6) has been in the minors the last two, the latest showing strong pace early but gathered in and finished a half a length second over 450m Shepparton in 25.63. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Deserves a win and gets his chance. BLUE BOY SHIRAZ (1) jumped quickly from box eight to score (22.42) two back then drew the same last time but settled off pace and could manage only a 10 length 5th at this track (24.55). Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from three starts. Has ability and can atone. SCOTT CHARISMA (5) boasts a solid strike-rate from this box.",
